{
  "stem": "39.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I don't know the-- exactly how many streets, but it was not a big area, of course.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They picked us up May the 3rd, 1944.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They came, the police, the soldiers, to each Jewish house, and brought us in with actually horse carts, and so on.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Of course, that was Hungary.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was the Fascist Hungarian police, gendarmes, actually.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And what we were allowed to take with us, each person was allowed to take one mattress.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were allowed to take some clothes, some dishes, some food, and some-- I don't know how, but we were allowed to take the radio also.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was May the 3rd, 1944, when they took us into the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, of course, the people from that certain area, they were evacuated who lived there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they were moved into our residences.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now you ask, how did we live in the ghetto?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Since it was a residential area, there were houses.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There were apartments, and so on.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Like where we lived, for example, that was a house.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The house had three rooms, one bathroom, one kitchen.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In each room, there were 10 to 12 people on our own mattresses on the floor.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Of course, there was no other way, no more room.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We were so crowded, 10 to 12 mattresses in each room on the floor, that whenever anybody had to get up, inadvertently, somehow who had-- he had or she had to step on the other person's mattress.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was no other way.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And one bathroom for 30 to 36 people, of course, it was not enough.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We always had to stand in line.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it was a miracle if one could take a shower.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was even a big deal to wash up.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We had to stand in line.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
